        "`MustContractDescriptor` in `contracts.go` returns a fallback descriptor when a contract ID is missing instead of failing fast; `actions.go` consumes this in contract construction, which can silently degrade contract metadata across module boundaries.",
        "README governance text explicitly requires maintaining descriptors in both files, indicating boundary correctness currently depends on process discipline rather than an enforceable runtime/build-time contract."
      ],
      "impact_scope": "subsystem",
