      "dimension": "cross_module_architecture",
      "identifier": "split_contract_registry_without_enforced_parity",
      "summary": "Action and contract registries are split across modules with no enforceable parity check.",
      "related_files": [
        "goseg/protocol/actions/actions.go",
        "goseg/protocol/contracts/contracts.go",
        "README.md"
      ],
      "evidence": [
        "`actions.go` defines action enums and per-namespace registration tables, while `contracts.go` separately defines `ContractID` and `contractCatalog` entries.",
        "Parity between an action token and descriptor ID is maintained by manual mapping (`contractForAction(...)`) rather than a compile-time or test-enforced invariant.",
        "README governance requires both files to be updated for protocol/error contract surfaces, confirming process coupling that can drift."
      ],
      "suggestion": "Introduce a single canonical registry (or generated map) that declares action token + namespace + contract descriptor in one place, then derive both action metadata and contract catalog views from that source; add a strict parity validator that fails tests/CI when any action lacks a descriptor or metadata entry.",
      "confidence": "high",
      "impact_scope": "subsystem",
      "fix_scope": "architectural_change",
      "root_cause_cluster": "manual_governance_over_runtime_contracts"
    },
    {
      "dimension": "cross_module_architecture",
      "identifier": "fail_open_descriptor_lookup",
      "summary": "Missing contract descriptors degrade silently due fail-open lookup semantics.",
      "related_files": [
        "goseg/protocol/contracts/contracts.go",
        "goseg/protocol/actions/actions.go"
      ],
      "evidence": [
        "`MustContractDescriptor` returns `ContractDescriptor{Name: string(name)}` when an ID is missing, instead of panicking or returning an error.",
        "Callers in `actions.go` use descriptor fields (`Description`, metadata checks) as contract truth; fallback descriptors therefore propagate incomplete metadata without an explicit failure path."
      ],
      "suggestion": "Change `MustContractDescriptor` to fail fast (panic in init-time paths) or replace with explicit `(descriptor, error)` plumbing in registration setup; add startup validation that rejects any contract entry missing required metadata fields.",
      "confidence": "high",
      "impact_scope": "module",
      "fix_scope": "multi_file_refactor",
      "root_cause_cluster": "manual_governance_over_runtime_contracts"
